\f2\b \cf7 \cb5 What works fine:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf7 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 All the form interactions, toggles, tooth grids, matrices, and print-hiding logic work perfectly on mobile Safari\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The "Print / Save PDF" button will trigger Safari's share sheet where you can save as PDF or AirDrop it\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf7 \cb5 What won't work on iPhone:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf7 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The\'a0
\f2\b "Email to me"
\f1\b0 \'a0button will fail silently or behave oddly. The\'a0
\f3\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 html2pdf.js
\f1\fs24 \cf7 \cb5 \strokec7 \'a0library relies on\'a0
\f3\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 html2canvas
\f1\fs24 \cf7 \cb5 \strokec7 \'a0which has poor support on iOS Safari \'97 it often produces a blank or broken PDF. Even if it generates something, the\'a0
\f3\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 mailto:
\f1\fs24 \cf7 \cb5 \strokec7 \'a0link opening simultaneously with a download tends to get blocked by Safari's popup restrictions.\cb1 \
\ls11\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 The\'a0
\f3\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf8 \cb9 \strokec8 mailto:
\f1\fs24 \cf7 \cb5 \strokec7 \'a0link on its own\'a0
\f4\i would
\f1\i0 \'a0open the Mail app, but the PDF generation part is the problem.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf7 \cb5 Best workaround for iPhone:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf7 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Use the\'a0
\f2\b Print button
\f1\b0 \'a0\uc0\u8594  tap the share icon in the print preview \u8594  "Save to Files" or "Mail PDF" \'97 this gives you a perfect PDF directly from Safari's built-in renderer, which is much more reliable than any JavaScript PDF library on iOS.\cb1 \
